 king on Christmas Day 1066.","url":"https://www.english-heritage.org.uk/learn/1066-and-the-norman-conquest/what-happened-battle-hastings/","urlTitle":"English Heritage - Battle of Hastings","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705183,"age":34,"year":"1086","julianDay":2117714,"title":"Domesday Book","description":"Domesday Book is Britain's earliest extant public record with information containing land surveys and landholdings commissioned by William I. The book was completed in 1086.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/domesday/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Domesday","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Baron William Malbanc was born in 1052, in Nantwich, Cheshire, England, his father, Alfred Malbedene, was 25 and his mother, Mrs. Alfred Malbedene, was 24. He had at least 4 sons and 1 daughter with Adelicia de Malbank. He died in 1086, in Nantwich, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 34."},"et":{"1052–1086":"1052–1086","1054–Male":"1054–Surnud","1060–1130":"1060–1130","1068–Male":"1068–Surnud","1079–1109":"1079–1109","1080–Male":"1080–Surnud","1082–1177":"1082–1177","1085–Female":"1085–Surnud","1027–Male":"1027–Surnud","1028–Female":"1028–Surnud","1080":"1080","before 1068":"enne 1068","1066":"1066","1054":"1054","1086":"1086","1130":"1130","1052":"1052","1085":"1085","1082":"1082","1060":"1060","1028":"1028","1027":"1027","1079":"1079","1068":"1068","1177":"1177","1109":"1109","Nantwich, Cheshire, , England":"Nantwich, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Oxfordshire, England":"Oxfordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Nantwich, Cheshire, England":"Nantwich, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Nantwich, Cheshire, England, United Kingdom":"Nantwich, Cheshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1052–1086":"1052–1086","1054–Male":"1054–Kuollut","1060–1130":"1060–1130","1068–Male":"1068–Kuollut","1079–1109":"1079–1109","1080–Male":"1080–Kuollut","1082–1177":"1082–1177","1085–Female":"1085–Kuollut","1027–Male":"1027–Kuollut","1028–Female":"1